You can design a RabbitOS-style platform to interoperate with many open-source and commercial LLMs, distributed AI systems, and networked algorithms by treating the system as an orchestration layer instead of a single monolithic AI. The key is modular standards-based integration.

1. Core Philosophy

Instead of:

One OS → One AI → One Model

Use:

RabbitOS Runtime
    ↓
Multi-Model AI Fabric
    ↓
Distributed Services + APIs + Edge Nodes

RabbitOS becomes:

an AI middleware layer,

orchestration framework,

telemetry router,

model gateway,

plugin ecosystem.


